free academic credits received can be obtained from the faculty mentor working with the cadet on the SURI project or from the department head of the department in which the research is conducted Room and Board  Cadets are required to find their own housing and pay for room and board Room and Board  Proposal Instructions Proposal Instructions The format provided below should be used for proposals for awards from the Summer Institute  Each cadet is required to submit an original proposal  even if the individual cadet is part of a team  The proposal should be written by the cadet and then reviewed by the faculty mentor and revised accordingly The format for proposals is The format for proposals is 1  Completed on line application form on line application form 2  A detailed description of proposed research project 3  A schedule for project completion  leading to completion of paper by the end of the summer school session 4  VMI and other facilities to be used 5  Statement of support from the faculty member  discussing the cadet s ability to conduct and complete this research  the importance and originality of the project 6  Endorsement from the department chair   Submission Deadline  Monday  February 15  2016 Submission Deadline Monday  February 15  2016 Monday  February 15  2016 Traditional SURI   DEADLINE February 15   EXTENDED TO 11 59 PM TUESDAY  FEBRUARY 16 Traditional SURI   DEADLINE February 15 Traditional SURI   DEADLINE February 15 DEADLINE February 15 DEADLINE February 15 Online abstract submission for traditional SURI proposals opens January 2016  Please submit your proposal at http web vmi edu suri http web vmi edu suri The deadline for traditional SURI proposals is 11 59 pm ET on Monday  February  15  2016  has been extended to 11 59 PM Tuesday  February 16  2016 The deadline for traditional SURI proposals is 11 59 pm ET on Monday  February  15  2016  has been extended to 11 59 PM Tuesday  February 16  2016 The deadline for traditional SURI proposals is 11 